svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616225\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616225\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104txj1665702628158.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/txj1665702628158.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/txj1665702628158.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"txj1665702628158\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property determines whether a three-dimensional appearance is applied when the widget is displayed. <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">True</code> (default) or <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txj1665702628158__p_d101456e1_d101457e1_d101458e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code> 3d <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">True</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">True</code>\n                     (default)</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__2\">Widget has a three-dimensional appearance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__2\">Widget has a 1-pixel black line as a\n                     border.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\"</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1__entry__2\">Use default.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"txj1665702628158__section_knj_tld_vwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d217219e131\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"txj1665702628158__table_d11948e1_d11949e1_d11950e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Dynamic?</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Yes, for Drag and Drop, OLE Container, Picture,\n                        and Tree widgets. <p class=\"p\">No, for all other widgets.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Supported in Grid?</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Dependencies:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Applicable only if <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Frame</span>\n                        is <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"txj1665702628158__section_zyd_wld_vwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d217219e186\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txj1665702628158__p_d101465e1_d101466e1_d101467e1\">This property has effect only if the\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Frame</span> property is selected. The 3D effect is purely visual; no\n            functionality is changed.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"txj1665702628158__section_vbd_1md_vwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d217219e198\">Check Box</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">For the check box widget, when <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>, a 3D effect is applied but only\n            the surrounding frame is in color, not the check box itself. If <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>,\n            both the check box and the surrounding frame are displayed in color.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"txj1665702628158__section_pfj_cmd_vwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d217219e214\">Using in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txj1665702628158__p_d101477e1_d101478e1_d101479e1\">For the Drag and Drop, OLE Container, Picture, and\n            Tree widgets, this is a dynamic property.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txj1665702628158__p_d101480e1_d101481e1_d101482e1\">You can use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$properties</span> or\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span> to set or get the property and its value. For\n            more information, see the \"$properties\" and \"$fieldproperties\" topics.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"txj1665702628158__pre_mhy_gmd_vwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldproperties(FLD) = \"3d=false\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txj1665702628158__p_d101483e1_d101484e1_d101485e1\">For other widgets, this is a static property. It\n            cannot be set in ProcScript.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"txj1665702628158__section_oss_hmd_vwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d217219e238\">Example: Setting in an .ini File</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txj1665702628158__p_d101489e1_d101490e1_d101491e1\">You can set the default value for this widget\n            property in the application <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"txj1665702628158__pre_vkf_jmd_vwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[widgets]\n...\nColorBox=ucolorbox(font=editfont;frame=on;3d=on;dimmedbackcolor=off)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"txj1665702628158__section_ehs_jmd_vwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d217219e253\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"txj1665702628158__ul_ihh_mmd_vwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41132e1_d41133e1_d41134e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fxi1688449052174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxi1688449052174.html\" title=\"The ucheckbox widget enables the user to set a Boolean value in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called CheckBox, which is mapped to ucheckbox.\">ucheckbox (CheckBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41135e1_d41136e1_d41137e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zfr1695290811319.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zfr1695290811319.html\" title=\"Start the Microsoft Windows Color dialog box.\">colorbox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41138e1_d41139e1_d41140e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gzs1665702629046.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gzs1665702629046.html\" title=\"The (ucolorlist) widget displays a list of system or web colors for selection in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called ColorList, which is mapped to ucolorlist.\">ucolorlist (ColorList)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41141e1_d41142e1_d41143e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vmo1688449724415.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmo1688449724415.html\" title=\"The ucombobox widget combines an input field with a drop-down list. It allows users to select one item from a previously defined list, or enter their own data instead. It is applicable only to form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called ComboBox, which is mapped to ucombobox.\">ucombobox (Combo Box)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41144e1_d41145e1_d41146e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wrn1665702633674.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wrn1665702633674.html\" title=\"The DropTarget logical widget accepts input dragged from a DragSource, other Uniface application, or Microsoft Windows Explorer. The data that is transferred consists of a Uniface list.\">DropTarget</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41147e1_d41148e1_d41149e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fud1688450548955.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fud1688450548955.html\" title=\"The udropdownlist widget is a field-level widget that can display a list of valid options in a list below the input field, so that the user can select one. It is applicable only to form components.\">udropdownlist (DropDownList)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41150e1_d41151e1_d41152e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"klb1688454363706.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/klb1688454363706.html\" title=\"Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\">EditBox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41153e1_d41154e1_d41155e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ied1665702642247.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ied1665702642247.html\" title=\"The uhtml widget is a field-level widget in a form component that renders HTML code (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) or displays a web page (when the field value is a URL prefixed by an ampersand (&amp;www.mysite.com/doc/index.html). Uniface provides a logical widget called HTML, which is mapped to uhtml.\">uhtml (HTML Widget)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41156e1_d41157e1_d41158e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rez1688451198680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rez1688451198680.html\" title=\"The ulistbox widget is a field-level widget that displays an open list in which one or more values can be selected. It can only be used in form components.\">ulistbox (ListBox )</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41159e1_d41160e1_d41161e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gls1665702643795.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gls1665702643795.html\" title=\"The umap widget defines areas on an image that allow the user to interact by clicking on that area. It can only be used in form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called Map, which is mapped to umap.\">umap (Map)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41162e1_d41163e1_d41164e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bwv1665702644903.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bwv1665702644903.html\" title=\"The umeter widget displays the value of a Numeric field on a gauge for which there is a predefined range of values marked around the outer edge. Uniface provides a logical widget called Meter, which is mapped to umeter.\">umeter (Meter)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41165e1_d41166e1_d41167e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"svk1665702646925.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svk1665702646925.html\" title=\"The umonthcalendar widget displays a month calendar to enable the user to select a date. Uniface provides a logical widget called MonthCalendar, which is mapped to umonthcalendar.\">(umonthcalendar) MonthCalendar</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41168e1_d41169e1_d41170e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vvo1665702647716.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vvo1665702647716.html\" title=\"The uOcxContainer widget embeds a Microsoft OCX control into a form component, and maps OCX properties and OCX events to fields and triggers. You can use ProcScript to activate OCX methods and let the OCX control activate widget triggers to respond to OCX events.\">uOcxContainer (OcxContainer)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41171e1_d41172e1_d41173e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rdo1665702649920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rdo1665702649920.html\" title=\"The uOleContainer widget displays an embedded OLE object, enabling you to define links to OLE objects in Uniface applications.\">uOleContainer (OleContainer)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41174e1_d41175e1_d41176e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ddd1665702643397.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ddd1665702643397.html\" title=\"The uoutputbox widget displays streaming text data. The data may come from a specified Output Channel, or be explicitly added. By default, it does not listen to any channel. Uniface provides a logical widget called OutputBox, which is mapped to uoutputbox.\">uoutputbox (OutputBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41177e1_d41178e1_d41179e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rgn1665702634165.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgn1665702634165.html\" title=\"Image to use as the background image on the map widget.\">Image Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41180e1_d41181e1_d41182e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1665702650577.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1665702650577.html\" title=\"The uradiogroup widget displays a set of mutually exclusive choices as a group of radio buttons. Uniface provides a logical widget called RadioGroup, which is mapped to uradiogroup.\">uradiogroup (RadioGroup)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41183e1_d41184e1_d41185e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwk1688451210612.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwk1688451210612.html\" title=\"The urtfeditbox widget is used to display and edit text as Rich Text Format (RTF), which supports formatting such as font and color attributes, text alignment, indentation, and lists. Uniface provides a logical widget called RichEditBox, which is mapped to urtfeditbox.\">urtfeditbox (RichEditBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41186e1_d41187e1_d41188e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"foe1665702651174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/foe1665702651174.html\" title=\"The uslider widget allows users to edit a numeric value in a field by sliding an indicator in a set of a previously defined range of values. Uniface provides a logical widget called Slider, which is mapped to uslider.\">uslider (Slider)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41189e1_d41190e1_d41191e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lxs1665702651483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lxs1665702651483.html\" title=\"The uspinbutton widget enables the user to enter or select a numeric value by clicking a button to increase or decrease a value by a predefined interval within a predefined range. Uniface provides a logical widget called SpinButton, which is mapped to uspinbutton.\">uspinbutton (SpinButton)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"txj1665702628158__li_d41192e1_d41193e1_d41194e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gge1665702634237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gge1665702634237.html\" title=\"The utree widget enables users to view and navigate structured data as a hierarchy. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tree, which is mapped to utree.\">utree (Tree)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svg1665702629592.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Frame</a><p>Determines whether a border is displayed around the widget at run time. True or False. The default value depends on the widget.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zie1665702558978.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$properties</a><p>Return or set the current widget properties of a field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1705998763272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldproperties</a><p>Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616225\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616225\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "3-D Effect (3d) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 This property determines whether a three-dimensional appearance is applied when the widget is displayed. True (default) or False . \" 3d = True | False \" Value Description True (default) Widget has a three-dimensional appearance. False Widget has a 1-pixel black line as a border. \"\" Use default. Usage Dynamic? Yes, for Drag and Drop, OLE Container, Picture, and Tree widgets. No, for all other widgets. Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: Applicable only if Frame is True . Description This property has effect only if the Frame property is selected. The 3D effect is purely visual; no functionality is changed. Check Box For the check box widget, when True , a 3D effect is applied but only the surrounding frame is in color, not the check box itself. If False , both the check box and the surrounding frame are displayed in color. Using in ProcScript For the Drag and Drop, OLE Container, Picture, and Tree widgets, this is a dynamic property. You can use $properties or $fieldproperties to set or get the property and its value. For more information, see the \"$properties\" and \"$fieldproperties\" topics. $fieldproperties(FLD) = \"3d=false\" Copy For other widgets, this is a static property. It cannot be set in ProcScript. Example: Setting in an .ini File You can set the default value for this widget property in the application .ini file. For example: [widgets] ... ColorBox=ucolorbox(font=editfont;frame=on;3d=on;dimmedbackcolor=off) Copy Applies To ucheckbox (CheckBox) colorbox ucolorlist (ColorList) ucombobox (Combo Box) DropTarget udropdownlist (DropDownList) EditBox uhtml (HTML Widget) ulistbox (ListBox ) umap (Map) umeter (Meter) (umonthcalendar) MonthCalendar uOcxContainer (OcxContainer) uOleContainer (OleContainer) uoutputbox (OutputBox) Image Name uradiogroup (RadioGroup) urtfeditbox (RichEditBox) uslider (Slider) uspinbutton (SpinButton) utree (Tree) Related Links Frame Determines whether a border is displayed around the widget at run time. True or False. The default value depends on the widget. $properties Return or set the current widget properties of a field. $fieldproperties Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}